<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[170,795,666,1107]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Nothing is known about the species’ breeding biology, but based on measurements of testicle size of the seven collected males, breeding appears to occur during the end of dry season and the beginning of the rainy season, between September and November (
<tableCitation box="[631,716,1082,1107]" captionStart="Table 3" captionStartId="8.[170,220,218,243]" captionText="Table 3. Testicle measurements (in mm) of seven male specimens of Knipolegus franciscanus collected at Curral de Pedras between May 2016 and January 2017." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Table 3</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
